					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In guitar tabs, slides are done like this.<br /><br />5/7 (slide from 5th fret to 7th)<br />3\1 (slide from 3rd fret to 1st)<br /><br />5~~~ (vibrato)<br /><br />A bend is done like this<br />5b6 (bend 5th fret equivalent to the next fret, ie. 1/2)<br />5\4/5 (start 5th fret, tremolo bar dip down to 4 and back)<br /><br />I've also seen...<br />5^ (slight bend up and back down)<br /><br />Edit, I suppose b would be confusing, since it's also used for flat notes.<br /><br />Also..<br />&lt;  volume swell<br />&gt;  volume fade</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://nesdoug.com" class="postlink">nesdoug.com</a> -- blog/tutorial on programming for the NES</div>
